laboratory_examinations.findings: Leukocytosis of 13.7 with neutrophil predominance (77.5% PMNs, no bands).

Multiple hypoenhancing liver metastases all appear slightly larger compared to the recent prior study. For example, the largest mass in segment VII now measures 42 x 29 mm (previously 35 x 23 mm), and a mass in segment V now measures 47 x 46 mm (previously 44 x 39 mm). Small bilateral pleural effusions are new.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Liver masses were noted to have slightly increased in size compared to the recent prior study.
